{
  "texts": [
    "We found a smaller proportion of differentially expressed orthogroups unique to each population than we found when examining individual genes, for both pathogen treatment (Mean % unique = 28.9, SEM % unique = 1.2; t-test, p-value < 0.001) and R/S phenotype (Mean % unique = 32.3, SEM % unique = 2.6; t-test, p-value < 0.05).",
    "Average LFC among orthogroups, however, was again only weakly correlated across populations (Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "Thus, each population used different, but often evolutionarily related genes to respond to P. palmivora.Few studies have examined defense response across many genotypes from multiple populations.",
    "However, our results contrast at least one recent study in Arabidopsis, wherein the evolution of immunity-related gene expression was tested by treating A. thaliana and its close relatives with the microbial elicitor flg22.",
    "Of the genes differentially expressed in response to flg22, the proportion of 1:1 orthologs unique to each species was approximately 20-31% [107]."
  ]
}